formatted_address: 501 Bukit Timah Rd, #01-01 Cluny Court, Singapore 259760
name: Da Paolo Gastronomia - Bukit Timah

reviews.text: Another shop we popped by to grab some food and coffee for a picnic. The buns are okay, but the selections they have is quite amazing (especially for breakfast). Surprisingly, the site is pretty baby friendly.

Had some desserts last night, were too good! The valrhona chocolate one and the hazelnut one, both were yum :)
We had the sandwiches before once and they were tasty but a bit dry.
Oh, the aperol spritz is quite refreshing for the hot afternoon!

Edit: good breakfast set, the blueberry scone was yum!

Normal cafe food, but quite expensive. The food wasn’t amazing but the vibes were quite nice, and even got a charging outlet to charge my devices. I don’t mind going back for the vibes but not necessarily to eat here !

food good (the vegetable pizza) atmosphere very nice, staff v friendly
oh & got free water.

BUTT damn ex + the SMOKED salmon pizza they baked abit too long when reheating. turn into cooked salmon pizza not nice liao. lucky this place got free water if not I will rate it 3 star

Got the protein bowl for lunch and it’s not too bad as the ingredients were nicely cooked, and the portion was decent. Price is on the higher side in my opinion but the ambience here is good and the service is prompt and decent too.
